To Everyone,



Very good points of view and healthy diversity. I will say, I apologize for
using the term.aheeemm Balls..

But the rest I was trying to say light-hearted, sticking up for us women in
general..

(that&#39;s not so bad, now is it?)

But what I meant, in a dry sense of humor way, didn&#39;t come across that way
to some, again I apologize.

But, I didn&#39;t ban Bruce, I only took away his right to post, anyone remember
seeing the other Mod wanting to ban him? They said I was being too nice.
Does anyone remember that? Also in the message I sent I also praised Bruce,
telling what a great job he&#39;s doing or he&#39;s so good with what he does,
nobody remembers that? 

Then I get bashed, I mean bashed..my personality, my work, my whatever. Then
someone sticks up for me from the bashing and they got slaughtered, and got
in the crossfire. I am sorry that Bruce is unable to control his bashing,
abusive language, insults remarks and threats to other people&#39;s lives. Yes
you heard me. I have the emails to prove it. Now, I am saddened this had to
be done, you may not believe me, but that doesn&#39;t matter anymore. I respect
all here. I respect Frank S, and he knows that. 

And I am sorry, that Bruce has to be so abrupt and harsh to fast too. Yes we
can be our own worse judge.



Again I apologize..Ann, great story..do I get paid for that part in the
movie?  I was trying to remember the actor that played a similar role in a
movie, with Sharon Stone. ( I&#39;m just joking) but really that was a good
little story that made up there. It was cute. J



LK







From: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com [mailto:EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com] On Behalf Of
lisbyfarrum
Sent: Friday, February 08, 2008 11:46 PM
To: EVP-ITC@yahoogroups.com
Subject: [EVP-ITC] Re: First Files from my new Frank&#39;s box #29



Steve,

I certainly respect and support the idea that none of us is a messiah
and none of us has all the answers, but that is not germane to the
issue here. This is about how to correctly and fairly moderate a list.

If this was the wild west, things would have transpired something like
this:

Bruce stood in the public street and offered a completely legitimate
exchange with the townsfolk.

Laura walked out of the saloon and took a shot at Bruce and at the
window of Frank S&#39;s telegraph office.

Bruce shot back at Laura.

Johnny Marlboro stepped out onto the balcony of the Imperial hotel and
took a shot a Bruce.

Bruce shot back.

Laura pulled out a deputy&#39;s badge, stuck it to her lapel, and shot
Bruce dead.

Ann ran out into the street and said, &quot;Don&#39;t you think there&#39;s a
problem here? Maybe the sheriff needs to step in,&quot; to which Laura,
acting under the color of law, replied that if Ann didn&#39;t like it she
could leave town and if she stayed she better not question authority
again. 

That&#39;s what happened here. That&#39;s the issue.

I&#39;m still standing here saying something is wrong. Shoot me.

Ann

